Exercise 13.14: Assume that numbered is a class with a default constructor
that generates a unique serial number for each object, which is stored in a
data member named mysn. Assuming numbered uses the synthesized copycontrol
members and given the following function:

void f (numbered s) { cout << s.mysn << endl; }
what output does the following code produce?

numbered a, b = a, c = b;
f(a); f(b); f(c);

Answer:
f(a),f(b),f(c) will have the same output.

Exercise 13.15: Assume numbered has a copy constructor that generates a
new serial number. Does that change the output of the calls in the previous
exercise? If so, why? What output gets generated?

Answer:
Yes it will effect the output since the copy constructor will be called each time we call f then s.mysn will
be unique and will print the serial number of a with 3 added to it, then 4 and 5(a+3,a+4,a+5).

Exercise 13.16: What if the parameter in f were const numbered&?
Does that change the output? If so, why? What output gets generated?

Answer:
The output will change  from the serial number of a with 3 added to it, 4 and then 5, instead the serial number of a will
be printed then serial number of a + 1 and serial number of a + 2 since we don't copy numbered when calling f.
